{"id":14881049,"mediaExerciseId":"ba90aa4e-06c6-40e1-b292-d1fa1bd9d680","exerciseName":"15","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612312,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":233,"solutions":[{"id":5989476,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This task asks to explain **why long-term bonds look similar to junk bonds. We have to compare and find the similarity between those two types of bonds.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":99,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/b0f2a45fc03e63d5e3df23e9451031a6/5b2f1b526646fc29da4900df2e554382/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":50,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/b0f2a45fc03e63d5e3df23e9451031a6/5b2f1b526646fc29da4900df2e554382/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**A junk bond** is a term for debt that is very likely to fail and never be paid. This debt was issued by risky firms in the past that faced a problem of growth industries. Economists consider that if the debt is ranked lower than BB by S&P Moddy's or Ba is part of these highly risky bonds called junk bonds.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Under normal circumstances, the maturity of the bond should not exceed 30 years. The companies issue such a bond because they want to keep the historically low-interest rate. **The time is so long, and we do not know whether the investor will survive or die**. Maybe the investor will never receive his investment back. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":174,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/b0f2a45fc03e63d5e3df23e9451031a6/e906642e68c2843f3a316c54d87421bf/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":89,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/b0f2a45fc03e63d5e3df23e9451031a6/e906642e68c2843f3a316c54d87421bf/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"**Junk bonds hold a high risk of failure, and because of the debt riskiness of the company, they may never be paid back. 100-years issued bonds maybe will never be paid to the investor because the bond maturity is longer than the investor's life.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":138,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/b0f2a45fc03e63d5e3df23e9451031a6/0135dff387c7ad9318afedc6b2a4ff18/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/b0f2a45fc03e63d5e3df23e9451031a6/0135dff387c7ad9318afedc6b2a4ff18/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"8dc896f2-74d6-4727-aa62-071cab8bc2b9","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881050,"exerciseName":"1","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"3171d375-6597-471b-b108-6d35f0bf1a1a","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/tex